<item>
            <title>[HBASE-767] Add option so stop-processing if &apos;lost&apos; data files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-767</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-646&quot; title=&quot;EOFException opening HStoreFile info file (spin on HBASE-645 and 550)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-646&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-646&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-766&quot; title=&quot;FileNotFoundException trying to load HStoreFile &amp;#39;data&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-766&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-766&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; are about handlers for the case where store file &apos;data&apos; goes missing.  This issue is about figuring why/how they disappear&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12400855">HBASE-767</key>
            <summary>Add option so stop-processing if &apos;lost&apos; data files</summary>
