                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12616204" author="stack" created="Wed, 23 Jul 2008 18:21:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should at a minimum add an option where we do NOT just log and keep going when a data file has been lost.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12621968" author="stack" created="Tue, 12 Aug 2008 20:46:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, hbase-766 was not about &apos;lost&apos; files in the end. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Edit this issue&apos;s subject so its about adding an option where we stop processing if data file goes missing rather than just log it and press on as we currently do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12968960" author="stack" created="Tue, 7 Dec 2010 20:40:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No longer valid and besides we have a flag in WAL that can be set to abort if data loss or log and carry-on.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
